1:41 p.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by defendant, has received an offer and will be accepting.  DA recites plea agreement, will amend to misdemeanor possession of THC with a fine and costs.  Defendant concurs.  Court goes over right to counsel.  Defendant waives right to counsel.  Court accepts waiver.  

Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  Defendant enters a plea of GUILTY to the amended charge.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty to the amended charge.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Sentencing statement by DA.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:  $200 fine plus costs.  Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or payment plan.

Clerk questions regarding statute number.  Statement by DA, same statute just misdemeanor possession of thc.

Court adjourned at 1:47 p.m.
